HEADWORD: Jub
<hw>Jub</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Perh. corrupted fr.
<ets>jug</ets>.]</ety> <def>A vessel for holding ale or wine; a
jug.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

